<TITLE> Heytens to be ADB country director from July </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 16 (bdnews24.com) - Paul Heytens is to take over as the new country director of the Asian Development Bank for Bangladesh, an adviser said Monday. Heytens is now working as the ADB resident representative in Nepal and will begin his Bangladesh stint in the first week of July. A seven-member delegation led by Kunio Senga, director general of ADB's South Asia Department, met finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam at the finance ministry. Heytens was part of the delegation. After the meeting with the delegation, the adviser and Paul Haytens met exclusively. The adviser told reporters, "Paul Heytens will work as the new ADB chief for Bangladesh. That's why we had an exclusive meeting." The tenure of present ADB country director Hua Du has already expired, an ADB official said. bdnews
